Good job Mr Cruise, now be a bro and give us Legend 2 after Top gun 2. Go back to fantasy and give us a badass sequel to a greatly underrated film that's just as influential on the fantasy genre as Blade runner is for cyber punk and sci fi.  LEGEND 2 with practical effects, a Mo cap darkness like thanos and an epic show down for the fate of whatever realm Legend takes place in. With princess lily dead and jack has been king, then something akin to the long night occurs when both unicorns or some other new being is destroyed. Something along those lines. Blade runner 2049 had elements that totally reminded me of Legend. Made me want to see a sequel.  Legend 2 directed by Denis Villeneuve. My god that would be mind blowing. All things are lawful for me,  but I will not be brought  under the power of any. text: The world's best action hero is back with a bang. I'm a die-hard fan of mission impossible series ever since I've watched mission impossible 1. Henry cavill will be playing the role of a Cia agent august walker who's been authorized to hunt Ethan and kill him as he's a skilled assassin not an observer. But Still Ethan Hunt is smarter, highly skilled and faster than August walker. After all he's a brilliant strategist and accomplished field agent in imf (impossible mission force). I've already planned to watch this fast paced action film with my little brother in imax 3d. Tom cruise is definitely going to nail his iconic role of a imf agent who'll do anything to protect his wife Julia, Benji, Luthor Stickwell and all of them from soloman lane. I'm looking forward to watch it for sure. The trailer is awesome, breathtaking and fantastic. I'm sure it will be another highest grossing film in the illustrious career of Tom cruise. text: Fun fact this movie is the reason that in the cinematic debut of the freaking Justice League, team leader/figurehead Superman had that super distracting CGI baby mouth and upper lip. You see Henry Cavill was filming this movie which required him to have that ugly mustache.  When it came time to do reshoots for Justice League Paramount  pulled a dickish power play and said he couldn't just shave it and wear a fake mustache for this movie's reshoots. So Cavill had to have his contractually obligated mustache digitally covered up, the effect was not convincing.   And now you know why what should have been the epic coming together of the Justice League, was turned into "Jesus Christ what the hell is wrong with Superman's face?"  Because Paramount Pictures decided to be dicks for their long in the tooth, overrated, only existing so Tom Cruise has an excuse to almost kill himself on screen, mediocre film series.

text: Watched Mission Impossible:Fallout Today...Awestruck....One of the most impressive action movies I have ever seen...Words wouldn't suffice to describe the visual spectacle..The full throttle approach by director Christopher McQuarrie  will sent shivers down your spine.The stunts leave you breathless, the acting is well done, and the cast dynamic is better than ever.I can’t  get this film out of my head and hope Cruise and the cast get the recognition they so truly deserve.Tom Cruise with his swashbuckler swagness is willing to die for your entertainment. This movie would have been just another action flick without Cruise. Sure we have a stellar cast, but did not Mr. Cruise steal every scene? He is perfect in the role of Ethan Hunt, a spy whose whole team is rubbed out in a convoluted cover up at the start. It is up to Ethan to uncover the plot behind the failed mission. The movie is a series of unveiled plot twists that becomes implausible after a while. But that's not the fun behind Mission Impossible. The fun is watching the great action scenes with their suspenseful turns. So much so, we are willing to suspend disbelief to enjoy the ride. And to let ourselves be swept away by Mr. Cruise's undefinable quality to take us there.And the stunts are performed by Tom Cruise himself. The daring set pieces are well choreographed and acted in a way that looks real and genuine that puts most of this year's other action blockbuster movies to shame. Halo Jump-.One of the first stunt scenes in the film, it is not just another jump. In the film, Henry Cavill's August Walker and Cruise's Ethan Hunt get hit by a lightning bolt as they take the jump. Due to which Walker loses consciousness as well as his O2 cylinder. What transpires on screen next is heart-stopping, to say the least. And let me remind you all, it's no CGI but Tom Cruise. The toilet fight sequence will leave you spellbound. How I wish this scene was longer in length than it already was. To see Tom Cruise and Henry Cavill getting reciprocated by one man is oddly satisfying and hilarious to see. The paris chase scene-.Who doesn't love Tom Cruise on a bike? Give the man a bike and he'll give the best bike chase scene you have ever seen. This one is too thrilling to be real but Cruise cruises past the busy roads of Paris like a cakewalk.Director   Christopher McQuarrie uses gliding camerawork and razor-sharp cutting to heighten the excitement of Hunt’s improvisation, which results in a car-and-truck chase down the very narrow streets of Paris, followed by some white-knuckle motorcycle work by Cruise; his ride through a roundabout, seemingly sliding within inches of dozens of other vehicles, is truly terrifying.Helicopter Chase-In the climax of the film, Tom Cruise goes behind Henry Cavill in what turns out to be an edge of the seat chase sequence and probably the best chopper sequence seen in any film till date. And what makes it even better is that Tom Cruise learnt how to fly a chopper to bring authenticity to the scene. I can watch this film again just for this epic climactic sequence.Foot Chase-It's Tom Cruise and he is running, enough said. But what makes this scene iconic is the fact that he broke his ankle while filming this scene.  This whole long sequence is one of the major highlights of the film and has been shot beautifully.Its a must watch.Don’t miss it.My rating is 10/10. And don't waste your time reading this article, go and watch the movie as soon as you can. It's totally worth it.

text: Mission Impossible Theory:  Before Fallout  August Walker wanted to be part of the CIA crew as an assassin, the reason is because (back then) he had a wife and one happy child and he was very protective when it comes to any intruders lurking at his family. One day he realizes that with him being protective he can be part of a highly trained crew that never lets a bad guy get away from the law big time like the CIA crew. He told his wife that he's planning to join the CIA but she didn't like the idea because of one thing, she hates sacrifices being made by one person that you love the most. August tried making her understand that this is what he wants to do to never lose his wife and son but at the same time she  didn't want to lose him. The two started an argument on not having an agreement on one person's idea and at the same time not fully understanding one person's feeling. After the argument his wife couldn't handle on having a husband that doesn't completely understand  So she along with her son left him. August felt bad but still feared on losing them. 4 Months later after training he became an assassin partner for Ethan and his crew. Times have passed for August fighting bad guys and hoping that his family is okay still.

text: Fallout is truly phenomenal, it is not only the best mission impossible film, but the best a mission impossible film can be. I've never seen such a fantastic film in a theater, its story is perfect. It has so much detail to it and i was locked in the entire time,  it was so complex that I must see it again to fully understand the detail in the script. The main problem with most of the mission impossible films is the characters. But in Fallout, it takes the characters, and makes them so likable that you want them succeed. An early film this year, Avengers: Infinity War, Has a great characters. But it has likable characters because of 18 movies of build up. Fallout has 5 movies, that didn't develop the characters that much, and this movie makes the characters so just likable and interesting. The visuals in this movie. OH MY GOD D*MN F*CKING GOD!!!! They were AMAZING. There is so much to a film that is in a era, were these stunts could be done easily with green screen and CGI, that is entirely practical. Every action scene is so thrilling and well shot that I was in shock. This film was brilliant in the camera angles that my jaw dropped. The 3rd act is shot so well and it is incredibly thrilling. The visuals are phenomenal. This movie, and this is gonna sound dramatic, but this is the best action movie I've ever seen. Die Hard, Indiana Jones, The Matrix, The Incredibles, The Dark Knight, Inception, Mad Max: Fury  Road, Fallout is better than them all, it is truly spectacular to see Fallout.

text: Best action movie I've watched so far. I don't go cinemas often, and when I do, I prefer action or supernatural themes because they give the best experience when watched on the big screen - Fallout gave the ultimate experience on that matter, there was action all the way. I'm no expert but I'll give it a 10 out of 10! One of the things I really liked about this movie was that it didn't contain any intimate scenes. I'm so sick and tired of the fact that almost every movie nowadays contains at least one erotic scene. Oh, and thanks for including Henry Cavill in the cast, he did great as a villain, and oh my did that mustache suit him (and I can't stand mustache on men!). I'll definitely watch it again someday, probably more than once.
